{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboardkitpro\/app-article"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboardkitpro\/app-article"]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"blue"},"modules":[{"name":"KeyboardKitPro"}],"title":"App Utilities","roleHeading":"Article","images":[{"type":"card","identifier":"Page.png"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has utilities that simplify building a great main app for your keyboard, like setting settings to sync between the app and the keyboard, auto-registering your KeyboardKit Pro license, and much more."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"👑 ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" unlocks app screens for the main app target. Information about Pro features can be found at the end of this article."}]},{"level":2,"text":"Keyboard App Namespace","type":"heading","anchor":"Keyboard-App-Namespace"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" struct that is also a namespace for app-related types and views, like the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/HomeScreen","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/SettingsScreen"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/LocaleScreen","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" screens that are unlocked with KeyboardKit Pro."}]},{"text":"Keyboard App","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Keyboard-App"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The easiest way to set up KeyboardKit is to use a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp"},{"type":"text","text":", which can be used to define things like "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/name","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/bundleId"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/appGroupId","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/licenseKey","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/locales","type":"reference"},{"text":" for KeyboardKit Pro, ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/deepLinks-swift.property","isActive":true},{"text":", etc.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can create a static app value and add it to both the main app target and its keyboard extension target, to easily refer to it from both:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["extension KeyboardApp {","","    static var keyboardKitDemo: Self {","        .init(","            name: \"KeyboardKit\",","            licenseKey: \"abc123\",","            bundleId: \"com.keyboardkit.demo\",","            appGroupId: \"group.com.keyboardkit.demo\"","        )","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Your app-specific "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp","type":"reference"},{"text":" can also resolve other properties that you may need, such as a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/dictationConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". This will be used even more in future versions of KeyboardKit, so make sure to start using it today."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp\/locales","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" collection is only meant to describe which locales you "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"want","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to use in your app and keyboard. It will be capped to the number of locales that your KeyboardKit Pro license includes."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"text":"Keyboard App View","type":"heading","anchor":"Keyboard-App-View","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardAppView"},{"text":" view can be used as the root view of a keyboard app target, to set up everything it needs to use KeyboardKit.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To use it, just create a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp"},{"text":" value as described above, then pass it into the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardAppView","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" with your app content view:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@main","struct MyApp: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            KeyboardAppView(for: .myApp) {","                ContentView()","            }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This view will set up "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardSettings","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to use an App Group, register your KeyboardKit Pro license key, if any, and inject "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Keyboard\/State","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" types into the view, which means that you can access any state value like this:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct MyView: View {","","    @EnvironmentObject","    var keyboardContext: KeyboardContext","","    var body: View {","        ...","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can then change any states from any view within your app, to customize them to fit your need. These contexts will also be used by the KeyboardKit Pro screens that are described below."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"👑 KeyboardKit Pro","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"%F0%9F%91%91-KeyboardKit-Pro"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit Pro","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro","overridingTitle":"KeyboardKit Pro","isActive":true},{"type"